      "snowpackStructure": {
        "comment": "The snowpack has clearly settled and stabilised. On the surface, it freezes overnight in many places and softens again in the sun during the day. On the south side, firn conditions are already developing where there is still enough snow. Up to high altitudes, the snowpack is slightly damp, in medium altitudes it is partly wet to the ground. In shady slopes at higher altitudes, faceted crystals can be found deeper in the snowpack."
      },
